Microsoft has launched its new Surface Studio 2 all-in-one PC, which it has labelled “the ultimate creative studio”. The latest iteration of the Surface Studio is the most powerful Surface device ever, boasting dedicated Nvidia Pascal graphics and a high-end Core i7 processor. Microsoft has also boosted the fidelity of the Surface Studio 2’s high-resolution display, improving the brightness and contrast of the panel by 38% and 22% respectively. The display features 4,096 levels of pressure, making it an ideal canvas for Microsoft’s Surface Pen, said the company. Microsoft said its Surface Studio 2 is currently available for pre-order in selected markets, and will launch in additional markets next year. The Surface Studio 2 is available in three configurations: Upon purchasing the Microsoft Surface Studio 2, you will also receive a Surface Keyboard, Mouse, and Pen.    